ine": "Amora Beach Resort Phuket", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "Walker", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5103AQGCodIf0VCY_A/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1548057941598?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=DrX8vGV-ID7XJVpveBoDBo7B7khwgalzCNV-FPoYNaM", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "phil-walker-50a60b19", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAPT5RoBn9KfRziizlTBKotA066Q7zBWEpk", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQHFbFyqnioh_Q/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B56ZombJj6JYAM-/0/1761581244840?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=gqUipBkEirz7ADcXNX164p4LtDTK8lbxcnrIZx1vxbI", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQHFbFyqnioh_Q/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B56ZombJj6JYAM-/0/1761581244840?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=gqUipBkEirz7ADcXNX164p4LtDTK8lbxcnrIZx1vxbI", "publicIdentifier": "eddybrosse", "recommendations/0/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Emmanuel directly", "recommendations/0/date": "December 24, 2025", "recommendations/0/description": "I have known, worked, networked, collaborated with Emm on many projects over the past couple of years. What an encounter! \n\nHe is a true hospitality professional, close to people and the business at hand, thorough yet super creative. In my last consulting role, he was actually the ONLY professional I could get to create a team for our 11 F&B outlets, open them, run them and create our vibe / buzz with regular in-house events. Maybe this is thanks to his varied experience and personal curiosity, his personality... but you don't see many multi-faceted talents so often. If I can't, catch him while YOU can!", "recommendations/0/name": "Emmanuel Elix", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "General Manager/ owners representative at Shine Beach company limited", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/emmanuel-elix-522ab0a8/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABbxdeoB6ZnI5ZfuozGGdLaSlOOOMezMcy8", "recommendations/1/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Stephen directly", "recommendations/1/date": "July 11, 2024", "recommendations/1/description": "I was convinced at first by Stephen enthusiasm and proactivity. They both proved to true (and useful!) in the long run when we worked side by side at Collective Hospitality.\n\nStephen proved to be a strong hospitality professional, with good principles and a relentless drive. Yet, he was always eager to check on his progress and suitability, asking for regular feedback which was a very good point.\n\nI appreciated the friendly yet professional, focused and result-orientated relationship we had. We were able to challenge each other's ideas and perceptions in order to come up with best solutions for all; isn't that the true basis of a healthy team?", "recommendations/1/name": "Stephen Pinto", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Luxury Hospitality over 15 yrs l Hotel Operations l Sip or Drink Beverage Consultant I Pre- Openings", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephen-pinto-8baa6850/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAArV2Q4BILcvJbKEsW4_uWzy-87fKCQNiF4", "recommendations/2/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ was senior to Anas but didn't manage Anas directly", "recommendations/2/date": "May 2, 2024", "recommendations/2/description": "Anas picked up our offer to work with us in a fly, and what a great move that was for both parties! \n\nHe was amazing at creating the sense of community most travellers crave for nowadays (and that is so hard to create AND maintain). In Kata, he managed to boost our Booking.com score to 8.9 (from way below) ... it is a shame he could not stay longer to travel from one property to the next to fix them; we understand this was only a sabbatical few months for him and he had to go back to Europe.\n\nStill, he was professional at all times, despite the tempting party atmosphere around him (too many fail). His communication skills are top, gentle, open-minded, appropriate and always respectful.\n\nI am convinced that he's got great potential for a brilliant career in our fascinating industry. Now, would I employ him again? Oh yes! In a heart beat.\n\nSo, anyone lucky to grab his attention, secure him first or he will be snatched in a blink of an eye!", "recommendations/2/name": "Anas Hajlaoui", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Finance · Entrepreneurship · Business Development", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/anas-hajlaoui-a62581194/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAC2lkKoBKtuj2kSpfEnrpKx__bxgbGRZieY", "recommendations/3/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ was Andrea M. J.'s client", "recommendations/3/date": "May 29, 2020", "recommendations/3/description": "A  COUPLE of sessions is ALL it took to clear and sort out some very old issues still affecting me on my day-to-day work and life. Truthfully, it would have taken me years of therapy to get to the same results (I am talking from experience here!). Although I am not sure the effect / solution would have been as tangible or sustainable. Not only a typical session brings me clarity, but I get tools to keep it going stronger! And no need to go over painful memories, the very emotional bits and the like (no need for the tissue box, thanks). As for the most conservative of you, no! there is no magic involved either.\n\nOf course, this is done through such a candid, honest AND professional approach ... well, no brain can resist!\n\n'Thank you' is the understatement of the year (and the next)!", "recommendations/3/name": "Andrea M. J. Luoma, PhD", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "* Conversation Reimagined * Synergizing communication to profoundly transform teams and relationships", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrea-m-j-luoma/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALE8RUBGX9uAp5wqhijf2BNe8fe_naAA5I", "recommendations/4/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ worked with Deepak on the same team", "recommendations/4/date": "August 29, 2016", "recommendations/4/description": "I was quickly impressed by Deepak's focus, knowledge of the industry (processes,   standards, procedures). We were working for 2 different properties yet we shared trainings and meetings hence I got the chance to have a glimpse as Deepak as a professional.\n\nI believe that he's got the professional courage to take the right decisions for the business (whether popular or not), he doesn't take 'no' for an answer, he seems persistent (also very necessary in our roles) and has the drive to steer a business in the right direction.\n\nI would have liked to work directly with Deepak but never had the opportunity in our hotels or any other. Maybe one day?", "recommendations/4/name": "Deepak Vaid", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Year = 365 Opportunities", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/deepak-vaid-41a2082b/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAZCgFYB7cl5oyPI3aVInxLl5yIgpcs5K_Q", "recommendations/5/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Mostafa directly", "recommendations/5/date": "August 29, 2016", "recommendations/5/description": "I employed Mostafa at one of the two properties I was managing in the centre of Paris: the Emeraude Plaza Etoile Hotel.  Mostafa showed very good skills as a Receptionist. Professional in all situations, he held the hotel alone at night. Willing to do well, he strictly followed our night audit procedures, while welcoming our guests and dealing with their requests. He is not the kind of person who spares its efforts to accomplish a good job.  The job was done, communication was flowing, guests were very happy, I can only regret that he had to go back home to go to the army.  As a person, he is a good asset to a team: a good sense of humour, always positive, he blended very quickly with the team.   I am positively sure that Mostafa will do well and I look forward to working with him again", "recommendations/5/name": "Mostafa Abdelazim", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "New adventure", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mostafa-abdelazim-81710312/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAKBxNMBqXhWeihSHP9xXNUU6WzIhrLBtm0", "recommendations/6/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Flavie directly", "recommendations/6/date": "July 15, 2016", "recommendations/6/description": "I could not compliment Flavie enough for the amount of work she has achevied during her 3-month internship with us, at Campanile Dartford (UK):\n\n-\tFormalised our recruitment process with a professional interview grid\n-\tFormalised our onboarding process with\no\ta `welcome booklet‘, \no\ta `induction checklist‘ \no\tnew starters‘ objectives\no\ta booklet with all our role descriptions\no\tupdated our new starter form\no\tand `induction presentation‘ (with updated internal structure)\n-\tCompleted a full audit of our personnel files, re-organised them entirely, refreshed each one of us‘ details and filed away all outdated\n-\tPrepared, implemented, conducted, analysed and followed up our first internal survey\n\nWhat could I say? This is beyond my expectations yet she achieved a sustainable outcome for every objectives we had set her out to do initially … wow! \n\nTo share now a few of her qualities and skills: focused, impeccable work ethics (especially confidentiality which is so crucial in HR), respectful, easy to get along with, blend in easily and quickly, wins trust because trustworthy, self starter, autonomous and serious in her every day work … I have recommended her to one of my best friends who is RRH in car industry (managing 300+ employees). And of course, I would collaborate again any time!\n\nShould you require more feedback on Flavie, do not hesitate to contact me directly.\n\nEddy", "recommendations/6/name": "Flavie C.", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "Responsable formation chez DEKRA", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/flavie-c-536bba123/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAB6ctXoB-NNgWZ-5PVy5PYPIgqRLQ8JaLoE", "recommendations/7/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ worked with Wendy but they were at different companies", "recommendations/7/date": "October 12, 2015", "recommendations/7/description": "Our relationship dates back a few years now, and so much has gone on since. But Wendy remains consistently good spirited, available, professional and sharp (in her thinking and analysis). Unfortunately I mainly call her when I need, does that make me a bad person? Hopefully not, it just shows that I can rely on Wendy. She is also honest so when she cannot help, she would say so.\n\nWould I 'work' with Wendy again? Well, hopefully not too often because it would mean many more jumps in my career but should the need arise, she will be my first port of call!", "recommendations/7/name": "Wendy de Hallé", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Director at Marshall Human Resources", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/wendy-de-hallé-38716912/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAKD0NcB02Wbrgx2qS1HSJzgQZxHGavG7IE", "recommendations/8/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Antoine directly", "recommendations/8/date": "October 12, 2015", "recommendations/8/description": "Antoine has proven up to my expectations with his enthusiasm, sense of initiative, common sense, self-management too (he was very autonomous which was handy in a new opening!) yet even more creative than initially thought.\n\nHe formed bonds with the opening team very easily and was very eager to help at all times. He just could not say 'no'.\n\nSo all in all, it has been a very interesting and constructive experience for all and I hope he will take this with him for years to come. I have no doubt with regards to his future career success. ", "recommendations/8/name": "Antoine Aillet", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Communication manager at Côte Ouest Agency", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/antoine-aillet-4b82a48a/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABLof8wB_uHCNhZ1x6gcg0htcGMryfLfwoM", "recommendations/9/date": "April 13, 2014", "recommendations/9/description": "It is interesting that despite the distance, the number of time zones and the only-online environment, we quickly gelled. Bernard is a very insightful hotelier, with great soft skills and an amazing humble personality.\n\nLearning alongside Bernard meant lengthy discussions about our weekly topics to report in the classroom, a reliable support, a constant good morale and a wealth of experience. At no point did I feel ashamed of approaching him with sometimes silly questions or my own thoughts on what we were studying. Again, his humility made him a very approachable student, and now a great friend! I did miss him when he dropped to the following class as our conversations were a great part of the learning curve at Glion online.\n\nXiexie!", "recommendations/9/name": "Bernard F. R.", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "Global Hotelier/General Manager - Hotels, Integrated Resorts, Vacation Resorts, Private Clubs | Operations | Openings | Conversions | Marketing & Sales | Turnaround | Rebranding | Innovation | People Development", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/bernard-f-r-6078044/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADUvmcB2kGPW9UphLDCnGuAIySwgbJn6-w", "recommendations/10/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Bianca directly", "recommendations/10/date": "March 29, 2014", "recommendations/10/description": "B is a very focus and detail orientated Manager. I enjoyed working with her with her drive, relentless persistence and sense of consequence. We also started to talk about pairing emotional intelligence with cultural intelligence at the time, yet I have no worries that she is still growing as we speak.\nShe actually left Camden through our internal IHG network, and I am both confident and proud.\nLooking forward to working together again!", "recommendations/10/name": "Bianca Cissé", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "Learning and Engagement Manager", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/biancafeiereis/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAASsXQYB-NsFZDFitfwDIC8ihOpNTReJ64w", "recommendations/11/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ was senior to Yamini but didn't manage Yamini directly", "recommendations/11/date": "October 6, 2013", "recommendations/11/description": "J'ai eu le plaisir et l'honneur de commencer à travailler avec Yamini lorsqu'elle était stagiaire et m'aidait sur mes 2 hôtels. Ce n'était donc que du bonheur de la voir recrutée au Siège. \nSourire constant, bonne humeur, retenu, sérieux impeccable, l'attention pour le détail et le suivi professionnel ... tout y est!\nJe serais ravi d'avoir une autre occasion. Yamini is a great asset to any hospitality organisation, from the very best of Mauritius hospitable character she shows to all her professional qualities and skills she employs.", "recommendations/11/name": "Yamini Govinden", "recommendations/11/subtitle": "Market Team Manager, Indian Ocean Islands", "recommendations/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/yamini-govinden-7b565214/", "recommendations/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALxbvkBG3C2SE-HyVk3ixPp7ZCA43klmfc", "recommendations/12/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ worked with Anne-Pauline but they were at different companies", "recommendations/12/date": "October 13, 2012", "recommendations/12/description": "Nous avons fait connaissance à ALICE et grâce à la connectivité réseaux d'Anne-Pauline. Ses qualités ont fait le reste pour fidéliser les parrains, les liés, réussir les rencontres avec les parrainés et assurer une légitimité à l'association aux yeux des institutionnels et tous professionels. Jetées pêle-mêle (parce qu'il est difficile de les classer), ses qualités sont: sourire, soutien infaillible, douceur, professionalisme, capacité d'écoute, patience, résilience et persistence, forte volonté, désir d'améliorer le quotidien des autres et soi-même. Je pense en oublier, mais à vous de les découvrir!\nNous sommes maintenant amis, mais une nouvelle collaboration n'est jamais exclue.", "recommendations/12/name": "Anne-Pauline ARENE", "recommendations/12/subtitle": "Oui, tant de rivières à traverser !", "recommendations/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/arene/", "recommendations/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAxzJlUBWABgYpYwoozPWnwK24Kw6U3lX9E", "recommendations/13/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ was senior to Amber but didn't manage Amber directly", "recommendations/13/date": "August 12, 2012", "recommendations/13/description": "What do they say about the caterpillar changing into a (strong) butterfly? 10 months of intense collaboration, developing each other, setting up and implementing our social media strategy, keeping current, focusing on essentials and getting our online branding right, one fabulous hotel video (she directed for us), a whole new series of picture shoot for the hotel (Director again) ... what a journey! \n\nI was convinced that Amber was definitely marketing material (so, not so much sales); she's got the feel, the touch, she listens and applies ... and most importantly, she's eager to keep learning (such a scarce drive!)! That a whole bright future out there, just for her.\n\nSo this is not a goodbye, more like the continuation of an exciting journey. I was sad to see her leave me all alone, but we've already got plans ... watch that space!", "recommendations/13/name": "Amber Virani", "recommendations/13/subtitle": "Marketing Operations, Paid Media & Analytics Expert", "recommendations/13/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ambervirani/", "recommendations/13/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAYskWoBOLpMtYs6vTWFbqv3sgw3qm1_d0s", "recommendations/14/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Ashish directly", "recommendations/14/date": "August 12, 2012", "recommendations/14/description": "Ashish takes ownership of his team and department to the extreme, while others don't even know how to spell it:\n- aligning every member\n- training, coaching and grooming\n- ensuring all aspects are being taken care of\n- scrutinising his cost lines\n... to the point of nearly wearing himself out. If he says he doesn't need help, he might still need a hand. \nThere was a lot of emotion on his leave: his guys were deeply attached and he was a central member of the team. But also that was the perfect move he needed, was hoping (and so was I). I was only worried he wouldn't get the support and further development he deserved.\nI am not worried about his bright future though and I would more than for sure work with him again, and again, and again ...", "recommendations/14/name": "Ashish Jha FIH", "recommendations/14/subtitle": "General Manager,Double Tree by Hilton, St Anne's Manor, Wokingham.", "recommendations/14/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ashish-jha-fih-65a47314/", "recommendations/14/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALqfuYBgnbIWl90iI4NCMBZdq-SWTSxMAE", "recommendations/15/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Amine directly", "recommendations/15/date": "October 18, 2011", "recommendations/15/description": "Amine sait ce qu'il veut et il ne refuse aucun effort pour parvenir aux résultats. Cultivé, brillant, c'est toujours un plaisir de converser et c'est toujours constructif. Il pratique aussi la critique constructive, ce qui est bien appréciable pour permettre à tout le monde d'avancer.\n\nCôté personnel: toujours impeccable, aimable, souriant, il ne s'énerve jamais.\n\nBref, un atout dans une équipe et je le reprendrais s'il voulait venir à Londres. Nous avons d'ailleurs commencé à entrevoir une collaboration!", "recommendations/15/name": "Amine R.", "recommendations/15/subtitle": "Officier de l'information et de la communication avec expertise en marketing digital et gestion de projets", "recommendations/15/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/amineroukhi/", "recommendations/15/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAZY_9UBZJDygJ_KQZk8_8CqJQC5MKWswhE", "recommendations/16/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ worked with Nadia but they were at different companies", "recommendations/16/date": "May 21, 2010", "recommendations/16/description": "I first met Nadia while she took over me at Somerset Queen's Gate Gardens. I think communication and a long lasting partnership was sealed there and then. \n\nBeing both scorpios might have helped a little: straight forward, honest, reliable, easy to connect with, no grey areas but a lot of passion in what we do or believe into.\n\nI find Nadia always easy to work with, ready to share sound insights of our industry and please to find a win-win situation for both.\n\nHer first steps within Grupo Albelmar are showing great work and passion, I am certain her efforts will be very fruitful.", "recommendations/16/name": "Nadia Bennouna", "recommendations/16/subtitle": "Business Consultancy | Executive Services | Project Management | Event Management", "recommendations/16/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nadia-bennouna-99629a8/", "recommendations/16/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAF3OgIBMP2Llt7O7u9HI1Mqc_3i9uFAWTg", "recommendations/17/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ worked with Christopher but they were at different companies", "recommendations/17/date": "May 16, 2010", "recommendations/17/description": "I see Chris is an unlimited source of information, great advices and energy. Very personable despite the distance and most probably the number of enquiries he gets.\n\nHis advices are always very practical, close to what we encounter. So he manages to stick to waht is the daily reality for most of us. No jargon. Calling a spade ... he shares widely and openly his great knowledge of online marketing, making cristal clear and easy to engage with for us.\n\nI would not tie the knot with him (I'm already married) however I am seriously thinking about more collaboration.", "recommendations/17/name": "Christopher Tompkins", "recommendations/17/subtitle": "CEO of The Go! Agency (Digital Marketing), Author, Forbes Council Thought Leader, Entrepreneur Magazine Contributor, Biz Journals Leadership Trust, Fast Company Board Member, Podcast Host, National Business Mentor", "recommendations/17/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/chrisgomedia/", "recommendations/17/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAMKNJMB-OTNQVkLLkt5H6vabjtOZvZLSn0", "recommendations/18/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ worked with Isabelle on the same team", "recommendations/18/date": "March 11, 2010", "recommendations/18/description": "Isabelle est une collègue sur qui l'on peut toujours compter. Importante source d'informations, elle a une grande expérience des acteurs de notre profession. Elle en gère d'ailleurs un large portefeuille, avec tact et dextérité malgré le challenge que certains peuvent apporter (notamment chez les Tours Operators).\n\nToujours précise, elle fait preuve d'un travail soigné et complet. Pas de promesse qu'elle ne tiendrait pas, c'est vraiment un plaisir de collaborer avec elle. Je la retrouverais avec plaisir dans une nouvelle mission.", "recommendations/18/name": "Isabelle S.", "recommendations/18/subtitle": "Consultant", "recommendations/18/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/isabelle-s-a7b02a10/", "recommendations/18/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAIjq38BoAWDctiMK6cxYGEYhYvIwxXtqqM", "recommendations/19/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Mostafa directly", "recommendations/19/date": "January 20, 2010", "recommendations/19/description": "I employed Mostafa at one of the two properties I was managing in the centre of Paris: the Emeraude Plaza Etoile Hotel.\n\nMostafa showed very good skills as a Receptionist. Professional in all situations, he held the hotel alone at night. Willing to do well, he strictly followed our night audit procedures, while welcoming our guests and dealing with their requests. He is not the kind of person who spares its efforts to accomplish a good job.\n\nThe job was done, communication was flowing, guests were very happy, I can only regret that he had to go back home to go to the army.\n\nAs a person, he is a good asset to a team: a good sense of humour, always positive, he blended very quickly with the team. \n\nI am positively sure that Mostafa will do well and I look forward to working with him again.", "recommendations/19/name": "Mostafa Abdelazim", "recommendations/19/subtitle": "New adventure", "recommendations/19/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mostafa-abdelazim-81710312/", "recommendations/19/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAKBxNMBqXhWeihSHP9xXNUU6WzIhrLBtm0", "recommendations/20/context": "Eddy เอ็ดดี้ managed Ekaterina directly", "recommendations/20/date": "February 13, 2009", "recommendations/20/description": "I thought about this recommendation over a few weeks. Finally, I can sum it up like this: I have unfortunately not found yet a Deputy half as good as Katia (and I'm now not sure I made the most of it at the time).\n\nKatia started as a Receptionist but quickly proved to be a perfect Guest Services Manager. She was part of the pre opening team at Roland Gardens, then we co-managed it. I was lucky enough to work with someone very professional and focused (both on guest' service and satisfaction, on finances and team management).\n\nI positively felt challenged, which I truly believe is a good thing for any managers. She was probably more financially astute than I was, only lacking some management experience she now has under her belt.\n\nWhen the opportunity arose for a 3 month training in Singapore (Head Office), her name came first with no hesitation.\n\nNow, after so many years within the Ascott Group, Katia knows about working under pressure. Furthermore she has managed her own residence, her own hotel. And I still follow her career with pride. \n\nIt is just a shame we live so far apart. I would more than gladly set up a \"winning team\" with her again.\n\nKatia", "recommendations/20/name": "Ekaterina Mjøen", "recommendations/20/subtitle": "People and Culture Manager", "recommendations/20/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ekaterinamjoen/", "recommendat