oto-shrink_800_800/0/1620564360147?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=dnbDMvAiKBPQbdi-l5K6vTWtZkaxtBd8bU4rRmrZEiQ", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5603AQFClaDue8v2RA/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1620564360147?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=dnbDMvAiKBPQbdi-l5K6vTWtZkaxtBd8bU4rRmrZEiQ", "publicIdentifier": "conny-johansson-61518939", "recommendations/0/context": "Conny was senior to Honey Ann but didn't manage Honey Ann directly", "recommendations/0/date": "July 17, 2014", "recommendations/0/description": "To Whom It May Concern\nI am writing this reference letter to recommend Ms. Honey Ann Hilario for the position Assistant Human Resources Manager or Human Resources Manager. I have work with in Island Hideaway and Atmosphere Kanifusi her and from what I can tell, she is totally perfect for this job.\nHoney Ann is a very responsible and dedicated person at work. She can handle multi task at the same time and never lets down our expectation. She is willing to take over new responsibilities at work without hesitation and consistently gives many creative ideas at work. During the time she was working for us, The projects she was assigned to were great successes.\nShe was a very valuable Assistant Human Resources Manager for our company. it was such a very pleasant and interesting time working with her. I believe she possesses just the skills and qualifications that an exceptional marketer should have as well as of a leader.\nI highly recommend Ms. Honey Ann for your company and, without doubt, believe that she will be such a great contribution to yours.\nSincerely,\nJan Conny Johansson", "recommendations/0/name": "Honey Ann Hilario", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Assistant Human Resources Manager", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/honey-ann-hilario-52951065/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA3Hn_EBZyRrsy5mjjRZyb4EAh60C27u_BY", "recommendations/1/context": "Conny was senior to Abhishek but didn't manage Abhishek directly", "recommendations/1/date": "July 17, 2014", "recommendations/1/description": "To Whom It May Concern\nIt is with great pleasure that I am writing this letter of recommendation for Mr Abhishek Anand who held the position of a Human Resource Manager in Atmosphere Kanifushi (EON Resorts).\nI can verify his strengths in managing work practices akin to hiring laws and practices. With a dominating personality and the ability to foster positive relationships with people he works with, he was very popular amongst his peers and supervisors.\nMr Abhishek Anand strength lies in his ability to manage accurate payrolls and relationship management which were the two most important areas of our company. He possesses strong public relation skills and a great ability to remain well organized at all times. Per my opinion, he will be an excellent choice to be the Director of human resource department practically anywhere.\nI believe that you will find Mr Abhishek Anand to be an excellent addition to your company – especially where professionalism and good ethics are concerned. If you need any more information regarding his work, please feel free to contact me and I will be happy to elaborate.\nKind regards\nJan Conny Johansson\njanconnyjohansson@hotmail.com", "recommendations/1/name": "Abhishek Anand", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Director - Human Resources at Hyatt Regency Delhi", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/abhishek-anand-9b5a3046/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAnDUJkBPBL9gRnuBy1o2QfuZ--IRGpSnHM", "recommendations/2/context": "Conny managed Ingo directly", "recommendations/2/date": "February 1, 2012", "recommendations/2/description": "This is to certify that Mr. Ingo Möller, born 15.05.1976 in Berlin, Germany has been employed here on Island Hideaway at Dhonakulhi Maldives Spa Resort & Marina a 5* luxury resort and a member of the\n“Small Leading Hotels of the World” with total of 50 luxury villas and private butler concept.\n\nFrom 14.01.2010 till 14.4.2011 in the position of a Executive Chef.\n\nHis tasks included the production of all kind of food, staff training, maintain the high food standards, buffet preparation and set up, duty roster for all outlets and food cost control as also in charge of the food order process. Over view off all 4 food outlets and steward operation on the Island, creating new menus for all outlets as well quality and consistency control of all kitchen operations.    \nMr. Ingo Möller was part of the kitchen team with 4 restaurants capacity of 150 pax.+260 pax. staff canteen restaurant .\nFurthermore, he is a hand’s on chef who leads by example, who can handle pressure and stress very well. He was very flexible and a outgoing chef who speaks to customer to assure the guest satisfaction in every way.\n\nWe learned to know that Mr. Ingo Möller was an open minded and interested young man who fulfilled his tasks to our fullest satisfaction and high standards furthermore always willing to go the extra mile!\nCommitment, diligence, calmness, prudence and tidiness distinguish the workmanship of Mr. Ingo Möller.\nWe would especially like to emphasize his extraordinary zeal, which was beyond the norm, as well as his endeavors for hotel matters and her keen interest to continually broaden her knowledge and skills in his field occupation. \n\nHis behavior was impeccable with regards to management level and colleagues. He is a great asset to any kitchen brigade and a 5 * Luxury hotel operation.\nI would hire Ingo Möller at any time again, his food is amazing and in a Michelin star level.\n\nKind regards\nJan Conny Johansson\nResort Manager\nIsland Hideaway \nMaldives", "recommendations/2/name": "Ingo Möller", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Director of Culinary & Michelin Star Pastry Chef || 31 Years in Fine Dining & Banquet Catering || Expert in Bakery, Pastry, Chocolate & Sugar Work || Innovative World Cuisine Specialist || Strong Leadership Skills", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ingo-möller-b469484/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADZ7GYB9BNQvkIC1lifq3NE4R2ujkah6gc", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Conny was senior to Honey Ann but didn't manage Honey Ann directly", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "June 25, 2014", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "I have known Mr. Conny for almost 3 years as his Human Resources. Conny and I worked together at Island Hideaway Resort & Spa and Atmosphere Kanifushi Maldives.\nConny is a highly motivated and qualified professional with experience in all aspects of resort strategies including sales, operational, and employee relations. \nConny has a unique ability to work in the space between management, sales and customer services. He worked well with all team members.  And I always wish him a great success in his future endeavor", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Honey Ann Hilario", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Assistant Human Resources Manager", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/honey-ann-hilario-52951065/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA3Hn_EBZyRrsy5mjjRZyb4EAh60C27u_BY", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Conny was Richard's client", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "June 9, 2014", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "I have gotten to know Conny primarily through the vendor side of the business over the course of two specific Maldives assignments, and without doubt Conny is very much the dedicated hospitality professional.\n\nTypically I’ve always found him to be extremely hands-on and possess extra-ordinary patience, tact and strong leadership skills  - very much a pre-requisite when tasked with handling so many diverse cultures - especially during the critical pre-opening phase. \n\nConny is a really solid operator and his focus has always been to ensure the team delivers an exceptional guest experience, and I sincerely wish Conny all the very best in his career path.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Richard Townsley", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Sales Director at Waterfalls Food & Beverages", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/richard-townsley-307b2376/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABAvG_cByJ_jmBk_dvh1D6h0OYs-cuACcWo", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Conny was senior to Abhishek but didn't manage Abhishek directly", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "May 31, 2014", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "I have worked with Mr. Conny Johansson in Atmosphere Kanifushi (EoN Resorts). Conny joined there as EAM - F&B and also was acting as Resort Manager. We worked togather in the preopening of resort and i was  impressed with his Human, analytical and Financial skills. Conny is hands on leader who always believes in finishing the work on time or before deadline. He takes care of his team very well and also motivate them to achieve the common goals. \nWorking in Maldives may bring isolation at times but Mr. Conny with his good leadership traits always keep the team motivated and energized. He has the ability of handling big team and he has thorough knowledge of resort operations.\n\nI wish him all the best in his future endeavors.\n\nIn case of further query do not hesitate to contact undersigned\n\nAbhishek", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Abhishek Anand", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Director - Human Resources at Hyatt Regency Delhi", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/abhishek-anand-9b5a3046/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAnDUJkBPBL9gRnuBy1o2QfuZ--IRGpSnHM", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Morten managed Conny directly", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "May 27, 2014", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "Conny is a very hands-on hotelier who is fully focused on creating great guest experiences. Operational tasks and the 